<div id="descriptionContainer">
  
      <div id="description" class="readable stacked" style="right:0">
        
<span id="freeTextContainer6025498502169476152"><i>Life and Fate</i> is an epic tale of a country told through the fate of a single family, the Shaposhnikovs. As the battle of Stalingrad looms, Grossman&apos;s characters must work out their destinies in a world torn apart by ideological tyranny and war. <br/><br/>Completed in 1960 and then confiscated by the KGB, this sweeping panorama of Soviet society remained unpublished until it was smug</span>
  <span id="freeText6025498502169476152" style="display:none"><i>Life and Fate</i> is an epic tale of a country told through the fate of a single family, the Shaposhnikovs. As the battle of Stalingrad looms, Grossman's characters must work out their destinies in a world torn apart by ideological tyranny and war. <br /><br />Completed in 1960 and then confiscated by the KGB, this sweeping panorama of Soviet society remained unpublished until it was smuggled into the West in 1980, where it was hailed as a masterpiece.<br /><br /><i>Librarian's Note: This is an alternative cover edition of ISBN13: 9780099506164</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="6025498502169476152" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

